cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) because it deals with understanding human language and extracting knowledge from unstructured textual data. It could also belong to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) because of the use of machine learning techniques to extract and represent knowledge. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category because of the focus on extracting knowledge from large-scale textual data. Finally, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) could also be a possible sub-category because of the use of neural networks in the extraction process.
